title: Unforgiven
overview: Retired Old West gunslinger William Munny reluctantly takes on one last job, with the help of his old partner Ned Logan and a young man, The "Schofield Kid."

title: Django Unchained
overview: With the help of a German bounty hunter, a freed slave sets out to rescue his wife from a brutal Mississippi plantation owner.

title: The Man Who Shot Liberty Valance
overview: A senator returns to a western town for the funeral of an old friend and tells the story of his origins.

title: High Noon
overview: A town Marshal, despite the disagreements of his newlywed bride and the townspeople around him, must face a gang of deadly killers alone at high noon when the gang leader, an outlaw he sent up years ago, arrives on the noon train.

title: Giant
overview: Sprawling epic covering the life of a Texas cattle rancher and his family and associates.

title: Mysterious Skin
overview: A teenage hustler and a young man obsessed with alien abductions cross paths, together discovering a horrible, liberating truth.

title: Gi√π la testa
overview: A low-life bandit and an I.R.A. explosives expert rebel against the government and become heroes of the Mexican Revolution.

title: Black Swan
overview: A committed dancer struggles to maintain her sanity after winning the lead role in a production of Tchaikovsky's "Swan Lake".

title: American History X
overview: A former neo-nazi skinhead tries to prevent his younger brother from going down the same wrong path that he did.

title: Midnight Cowboy
overview: A naive hustler travels from Texas to New York City to seek personal fortune, finding a new friend in the process.

title: Full Metal Jacket
overview: A pragmatic U.S. Marine observes the dehumanizing effects the Vietnam War has on his fellow recruits from their brutal boot camp training to the bloody street fighting in Hue.

title: Ordinary People
overview: The accidental death of the older son of an affluent family deeply strains the relationships among the bitter mother, the good-natured father, and the guilt-ridden younger son.

title: American Beauty
overview: A sexually frustrated suburban father has a mid-life crisis after becoming infatuated with his daughter's best friend.

title: Hiroshima mon amour
overview: A French actress filming an anti-war film in Hiroshima has an affair with a married Japanese architect as they share their differing perspectives on war.

title: Nelyubov
overview: A couple going through a divorce must team up to find their son who has disappeared during one of their bitter arguments.

title: Gifted
overview: Frank, a single man raising his child prodigy niece Mary, is drawn into a custody battle with his mother.

title: Blue Velvet
overview: The discovery of a severed human ear found in a field leads a young man on an investigation related to a beautiful, mysterious nightclub singer and a group of psychopathic criminals who have kidnapped her child.

title: Network
overview: A television network cynically exploits a deranged former anchor's ravings and revelations about the news media for its own profit.

title: Rain Man
overview: Selfish yuppie Charlie Babbitt's father left a fortune to his savant brother Raymond and a pittance to Charlie; they travel cross-country.

title: Philadelphia
overview: When a man with HIV is fired by his law firm because of his condition, he hires a homophobic small time lawyer as the only willing advocate for a wrongful dismissal suit.
